The paper deals with the mathematical modelling of DNA-based data storage as a communication channel and the design of error-correcting codes for this channel. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of sets and sequences, which are common in the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also deals with error control, which is relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
